-- ============================================================
-- LAYER 3: Weil Positivity Criterion
-- ============================================================

/-- Weil's criterion (1952): The Riemann Hypothesis is equivalent to
    the positivity of the Weil functional on autocorrelations.

    This is the form we will target. The entire project reduces RH to
    showing this positivity follows from the algebraic structure of ℤ.

    SORRY REASON: Requires Layers 1-2 (functional equation, explicit formula).
    DIFFICULTY: Research-level for the full equivalence proof.
    WHAT'S NEEDED: Analytic continuation of ζ, Hadamard product, contour
    integration, the explicit formula. -/
theorem weil_criterion_stub : True := trivial

-- ============================================================
-- LAYER 4: Product Formula = Arithmetic Detailed Balance
-- ============================================================

/-- The product formula: for any x ∈ ℚ*, the product of |x|_v over
    all places v (one for each prime p, plus the archimedean place)
    equals 1.

    This is the arithmetic manifestation of detailed balance:
    the total "flow" across all primes is zero.

    SORRY REASON: Need to verify if this is in Mathlib's adele ring theory.
    DIFFICULTY: Routine if adele ring infrastructure exists.
    WHAT'S NEEDED: Check Mathlib.NumberTheory.NumberField.AdeleRing -/
theorem product_formula_rationals_stub : True := trivial
-- Actual statement:
-- ∀ x : ℚ, x ≠ 0 → ∏ v : Place ℚ, ‖x‖_v = 1

-- ============================================================
-- LAYER 6: THE LEMMA (Statement Only)
-- ============================================================

/-- **The Arithmetic Hodge Index Theorem** (Conjectural)

    For any element α of the degree-zero arithmetic Chow group of
    the Arakelov compactification of Spec(ℤ), the Arakelov
    self-intersection satisfies α · α ≤ 0, with equality iff α = 0.

    EQUIVALENTLY: The Weil functional is non-negative on autocorrelations.
    EQUIVALENTLY: The Riemann Hypothesis.

    This is stated here as a stub. The full formalization requires:
    1. Arakelov intersection theory (Gap D in the directive)
    2. Arithmetic Chow groups (Gap D)
    3. Connection to Weil functional (Layer 5-6)

    SORRY REASON: This is equivalent to RH. It is the summit.
    DIFFICULTY: Millennium Prize level.
    WHAT'S NEEDED: See the full directive document for the reduction
    to Workpacket 5 (positivity of the geometric side of the Connes
    trace formula). -/
theorem arithmetic_hodge_index_stub : True := trivial

